FBIS4-53703 "dreas099_a_94039" FBIS-EAS-94-099 Daily Report 21 May 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Former Vice Minister To Head Livestock Agency Former Vice Minister To Head Livestock Agency OW2105024694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0228 GMT 21 May 94 OW2105024694 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, May 21 KYODO -- The Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries tentatively decided Saturday [21 May] to name a former vice agriculture minister for international affairs to head the ministry-affiliated Livestock Industry Promotion Corp., ministry officials said. Jiro Shiwaku, 61, will officially succeed the current president, Nobuo Imamura, on June 1, the officials said. Shiwaku represented Japan in the Uruguay Round of multilateral trade talks under the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade, which were concluded last December.
